This component:

Shows the centered intro line you wanted.

Uses your exact sentence:
"Hi! Letâ€™s turn your idea into an intelligent workflow."

Simulates Gemini â†’ n8n plan.

Reveals steps with animated â€œdropâ€ cards.

Includes "Open in n8n", credentials, and Run & Monitor guidance.

Uses the NUKI-style dark/yellow aesthetic and glass cards.

Includes footer with your signature.============
Built by El Houcine Idousaid 

==========================================
When I say WorkflowList, I mean the screen (inside the dashboard) that shows all the workflows the user has already generated with the AI.
Think of it like â€œyour library of automations.â€
Hereâ€™s what it needs to do and then Iâ€™ll give you full production React code for it:


Show each saved workflow:


Workflow name


Short description / purpose


Status (Draft, Active, Error, etc.)


Last updated date


Runs / success rate (basic stats)




Actions for each workflow:


â€œOpenâ€ â†’ view/edit it (or re-open in the ChatInterface view to regenerate/change)


â€œExport to n8nâ€ â†’ download the n8n JSON again


â€œRun & Monitorâ€ â†’ jumps to analytics (for v2)




â€œ+ Create New Workflowâ€ button at the top â†’ sends you to /workflow/new (the chat builder we already built).


This is exactly what your dashboard needs to feel like a SaaS, not just a playground.
Now Iâ€™ll give you two components:


DashboardLayout.tsx (the whole dashboard page shell with sidebar, header, footer)


WorkflowList.tsx (the actual list/table of workflows in that dashboard)


These are production-style React + Tailwind, aligned with the same dark / yellow / glass aesthetic youâ€™re using. You can drop them into frontend/src/components/dashboard/.

DashboardLayout.tsx
import React from "react";
import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom";
import {
  PlusCircle,
  BarChart3,
  FolderTree,
  Settings,
  Shield,
  LogOut,
  User,
} from "lucide-react";

type DashboardLayoutProps = {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  userEmail?: string;
  onLogout?: () => void;
};

