What this gives you:


Sidebar with nav (Workflows, Analytics, Settings, Legal).


Top bar with "Create New Workflow" button.


Footer with compliance links + â€œBuilt by El Houcine Idousaidâ€.


Slot {children} so you can render WorkflowList inside.


Now letâ€™s build WorkflowList.tsx.

WorkflowList.tsx
This is the table of â€œeverything the AI already generated for meâ€. In v1 weâ€™ll mock data. Later you'll load it from the backend (/api/workflows).
import React from "react";
import { MoreHorizontal, Download, PlayCircle, ExternalLink } from "lucide-react";

export type WorkflowStatus = "draft" | "active" | "error";

export type WorkflowItem = {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  status: WorkflowStatus;
  runsLast24h: number;
  successRate: number; // 0-100
  updatedAt: string; // ISO or nice string
};

type WorkflowListProps = {
  workflows?: WorkflowItem[];
  onOpen?: (id: string) => void;
  onExport?: (id: string) => void;
  onRunMonitor?: (id: string) => void;
};

const statusStyle: Record<WorkflowStatus, { label: string; className: string }> = {
  draft: {
    label: "Draft",
    className:
      "bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-300 border border-neutral-600",
  },
  active: {
    label: "Active",
    className:
      "bg-semantic-success/20 text-semantic-success border border-semantic-success/40",
  },
  error: {
    label: "Error",
    className:
      "bg-semantic-error/20 text-semantic-error border border-semantic-error/40",
  },
};

const WorkflowList: React.FC<WorkflowListProps> = ({
  workflows = [
    {
      id: "wf_001",
      name: "Zendesk â†’ AI Summary â†’ Slack Alert",
      description:
        "Summarize every new Zendesk ticket with Gemini and send priority alerts to Slack.",
      status: "active",
      runsLast24h: 132,
      successRate: 99.2,
      updatedAt: "2025-10-27 14:32",
    },
    {
      id: "wf_002",
      name: "Daily Ops Report",
      description:
        "Pull yesterdayâ€™s stats, generate a management summary, email it at 07:00.",
      status: "draft",
      runsLast24h: 0,
      successRate: 0,
      updatedAt: "2025-10-26 09:10",
    },
    {
      id: "wf_003",
      name: "Escalation Monitor",
      description:
        "Detect VIP complaints and alert on-call lead instantly if sentiment is negative.",
      status: "error",
      runsLast24h: 12,
      successRate: 75.0,
      updatedAt: "2025-10-25 22:41",
    },
  ],
  onOpen,
  onExport,
  onRunMonitor,
}) => {
  return (
    <div className="w-full">
      {/* Header row */}
      <div className="flex items-end justify-between mb-6 flex-wrap gap-4">
        <div>
          <div className="text-h3 font-semibold text-white leading-tight">
            Saved Workflows
          </div>
          <div className="text-neutral-500 text-sm">
            Your generated automations. Review, export, monitor.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div className="text-xs text-neutral-600">
          Data stays on your side.  
          We generate logic â€” you run it in your own n8n.
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Table container */}
      <div className="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-dark shadow-card glass-card">
        <table className="w-full text-left text-sm text-neutral-300">
          <thead className="bg-neutral-dark/60 border-b border-neutral-800 text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-neutral-500">
            <tr>
              <th className="px-5 py-4 font-medium">Workflow</th>
              <th className="px-5 py-4 font-medium">Status</th>
              <th className="px-5 py-4 font-medium whitespace-nowrap">
                Runs (24h)
              </th>
              <th className="px-5 py-4 font-medium whitespace-nowrap">
                Success
              </th>
              <th className="px-5 py-4 font-medium whitespace-nowrap">
                Updated
              </th>
              <th className="px-5 py-4 font-medium text-right">Actions</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            {workflows.map((wf, idx) => (
              <tr
                key={wf.id}
                className={`border-b border-neutral-800/60 ${
                  idx % 2 === 0 ? "bg-neutral-dark/40" : "bg-neutral-darkest/40"
                }`}
              >
                {/* Name + description */}
                <td className="align-top px-5 py-4">
                  <div className="text-white font-medium flex items-center gap-2">
                    <span>{wf.name}</span>
                    {wf.status === "active" && (
                      <span className="text-[10px] font-mono text-semantic-success bg-semantic-success/10 border border-semantic-success/40 rounded px-2 py-[2px] leading-none">
                        LIVE
                      </span>
                    )}
                  </div>
                  <div className="text-neutral-500 text-xs leading-relaxed mt-1 max-w-md">
                    {wf.description}
                  </div>
                </td>

                {/* Status */}
                <td className="align-top px-5 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">
                  <span
                    className={`inline-flex items-center rounded-lg px-2 py-1 text-[11px] font-medium leading-none ${statusStyle[wf.status].className}`}
                  >
                    {statusStyle[wf.status].label}
                  </span>
                </td>

                {/* Runs */}
                <td className="align-top px-5 py-4 text-neutral-300 text-sm">
                  {wf.runsLast24h}
                </td>

                {/* Success */}
                <td className="align-top px-5 py-4 text-neutral-300 text-sm">
                  {wf.successRate}%
                </td>

                {/* Updated */}
                <td className="align-top px-5 py-4 text-neutral-500 text-xs whitespace-nowrap">
                  {wf.updatedAt}
                </td>

                {/* Actions */}
                <td className="align-top px-5 py-4 text-right">
                  <div className="flex items-center justify-end gap-2 text-neutral-400">
                    <button
                      className="flex items-center gap-1 px-2 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-neutral-800 border border-neutral-700 hover:border-primary-yellow/40 hover:text-primary-yellow transition-all text-[11px] font-medium"
                      onClick={() => onOpen && onOpen(wf.id)}
                      title="Open workflow"
                    >
                      <ExternalLink className="w-3.5 h-3.5" />
                      <span>Open</span>
                    </button>

                    <button
                      className="flex items-center gap-1 px-2 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-neutral-800 border border-neutral-700 hover:border-primary-yellow/40 hover:text-primary-yellow transition-all text-[11px] font-medium"
                      onClick={() => onExport && onExport(wf.id)}
                      title="Export to n8n"
                    >
                      <Download className="w-3.5 h-3.5" />
                      <span>Export</span>
                    </button>

                    <button
                      className="flex items-center gap-1 px-2 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-neutral-800 border border-neutral-700 hover:border-primary-yellow/40 hover:text-primary-yellow transition-all text-[11px] font-medium"
                      onClick={() => onRunMonitor && onRunMonitor(wf.id)}
                      title="Run & Monitor"
                    >
                      <PlayCircle className="w-3.5 h-3.5" />
                      <span>Monitor</span>
                    </button>

                    <button
                      className="p-1.5 rounded-lg bg-neutral-800 border border-neutral-700 hover:border-neutral-500 transition-all"
                      title="More"
                    >
                      <MoreHorizontal className="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-500 hover:text-neutral-300" />
                    </button>
                  </div>
                </td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      {/* small compliance note */}
      <div className="text-[11px] text-neutral-500 mt-4 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Workflows are generated with AI (Gemini 2.0 Flash).
        Always review logic and credentials before running in production.
        You control your own n8n instance â€” we never execute on your behalf.
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default WorkflowList;

How it connects:


DashboardLayout wraps the page (sidebar, header, footer).


Inside DashboardLayout, you render <WorkflowList />.


The â€œCreate New Workflowâ€ button in the header routes you to /workflow/new which is the ChatInterface screen we already built.


Action buttons:


Open â†’ later can navigate to /workflow/:id


Export â†’ trigger download of that workflow JSON so user can import into n8n


Monitor â†’ later show analytics




Yes: â€œworkflow listâ€ = â€œlist of workflows the user already created with the AIâ€.
You now have landing, dashboard shell, workflow list, create workflow chat, export guidance, compliance footer, and your name in-product. This is already a real SaaS direction, not a concept.
